Employer should refer to their agency for guidance. Home health care aides are not eligible for benefits under the federal provisions, Family First Coronavirus Response Act (FFCRA). They are eligible for benefits under NYS Paid Sick Leave and NYC Paid Safe and Sick Leave. Home attendants and care workers who are not providng health care are elegible for leave under FFCRA. Nannies and cleaners have protections under FCRA. This benefit does not have any immigration status or minimum work requirements. These provisions last until Dec. 31, 2020.

Self Quarantine: {{employee_type}} is eligible for Emergency Paid Sick Leave Act, to a maximum of 80 hours, at their regular rate.Your agency or you (depending on your arrangement) are responsible for up-front payment, they may be eligible for a tax credit.

For a overview on how the new legislations affect domestic employers please visit: {{our FAQ|https://domesticemployers.org/covid-19-benefits-eligibility-faqs-new-york-city/}}
